entries.meaning: The act of weaving or forming again.
examples: On the Palingenesia, or New-birth of Society; which volume, as treating practically of the Wear, Destruction, and Retexture of Spiritual Tissues, or Garments, forms, properly speaking, the Transcendental or ultimate Portion of this my work on Clothes, and is already in a state of forwardness.

verbs.description: retexture (third-person singular simple present retextures, present participle retexturing, simple past and past participle retextured)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To give a new texture to.
